You will be safe?

258
00:23:01,295 --> 00:23:04,202
I'll go to my father's house.

259
00:23:10,621 --> 00:23:13,409
Nobody's answering the phone.

260
00:23:13,410 --> 00:23:15,248
Right, okay. Come on.

261
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:20,440
The front and back gates have been
fortified and the perimeter is secure.

262
00:23:21,595 --> 00:23:25,714
We are apparently hosting 400 - 450 refuges.

263
00:23:25,715 --> 00:23:26,948
Mostly Tutsi.

264
00:23:26,949 --> 00:23:29,246
We can't cope with many more.

265
00:23:29,247 --> 00:23:33,148
There will be more to come. They know
you are here, they’re looking for protection.

266
00:23:39,778 --> 00:23:43,770
My order is I'm not to allow this
school to become a safe haven.

267
00:23:46,182 --> 00:23:48,958
But you are peacekeepers.

268
00:23:48,959 --> 00:23:52,020
Surely you are here to prevent bloodshed.

269
00:23:52,021 --> 00:23:54,587
Peacekeepers? No.

270
00:23:54,588 --> 00:23:59,738
Our mandate is very clear. We are here to monitor
the peace between Hutu and Tutsi. That is all.

271
00:23:59,739 --> 00:24:02,364
Why did you bring all these guns?

272
00:24:03,793 --> 00:24:07,281
Our rules of engagement allow the
use of weapons only in self-defense.

273
00:24:07,282 --> 00:24:13,289
In fact to use the M-2 machine gun, I must even obtain
the approval of the Secretary General himsef.

274
00:24:15,408 --> 00:24:20,352
Our mandate is not to enforce the peace,
but to monitor it.

275
00:24:20,353 --> 00:24:23,466
Alright Capitaine, I can understand the difference.

276
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:26,502
Certainly these people won't.

277
00:24:29,539 --> 00:24:32,462
7th APRIL 1994

278
00:24:34,695 --> 00:24:37,584
7 hundred hours,
Greenwich meantime.

279
00:24:37,585 --> 00:24:41,294
Violence has broken out in the central
African republic of Rwanda,

280
00:24:41,295 --> 00:24:46,768
following the death of Hutu president Juvenal
Habyarimana in a plane crash, yesterday evening.

281
00:24:46,769 --> 00:24:54,127
Sources loyal to the government are blaming members of the local
Tutsi minority. They are suspected to attack the plane by rocket fire.

282
00:25:20,365 --> 00:25:23,238
White men coming in big car.

283
00:25:23,727 --> 00:25:25,919
To make whinings.

284
00:25:34,765 --> 00:25:40,190
Christopher, I need to put them
somewhere with facilities.

285
00:25:40,191 --> 00:25:43,869
Yes, of course.
We must have the facilities.

286
00:25:45,719 --> 00:25:48,405
Last time they had the old offices there.

287
00:25:48,406 --> 00:25:50,041
Thank you.

288
00:25:51,056 --> 00:25:54,010
- Isn't that nice?
- It's really nice.

289
00:25:54,979 --> 00:25:56,238
Can I use a tow truck for a while?

290
00:25:56,239 --> 00:25:57,481
For what?

291
00:25:57,482 --> 00:26:00,485
For Marie and Roland to bring them here.

292
00:26:00,486 --> 00:26:02,017
It's not a good idea.

293
00:26:02,018 --> 00:26:04,652
It's two roads there,
it would take a couple of minutes.

294
00:26:04,653 --> 00:26:06,527
Straight there and back.

295
00:27:22,638 --> 00:27:25,075
Hello? Anybody home?

296
00:27:31,484 --> 00:27:32,746
Hello, Roland?

297
00:27:35,129 --> 00:27:36,108
Marie?

298
00:27:42,017 --> 00:27:43,039
Roland?

299
00:27:46,127 --> 00:27:47,815
Marie?

300
00:27:52,797 --> 00:27:53,933
Hello.

301
00:28:52,663 --> 00:28:55,424
No, I'm a teacher.

302
00:29:23,158 --> 00:29:24,422
Okay.

303
00:29:57,752 --> 00:29:59,493
It's really weird out there, Christopher.

304
00:29:59,494 --> 00:30:00,494
And I didn't see anybody.

305
00:30:00,495 --> 00:30:01,814
That's strange.

306
00:30:01,815 --> 00:30:03,881
I'm gonna need your help in the chapel shortly.

307
00:30:03,882 --> 00:30:06,775
I couldn't find the Motagomas
and their house was empty.

308
00:30:06,776 --> 00:30:08,739
They're over there.
I saw them five minutes ago.

309
00:30:12,125 --> 00:30:15,883
Marie, where have you been?
I have just been at your house.

310
00:30:15,884 --> 00:30:18,872
We had to come back way.
They were road-blocks everywhere.

311
00:30:19,404 --> 00:30:21,862
Well you are safe now
and that's what matters.

312
00:30:21,863 --> 00:30:27,143
Listen, classrooms are getting pretty busy, why don't you
take my room? It will be much more comfortable for you.

313
00:30:27,779 --> 00:30:33,111
Thank you, Joe. But, you see, many of our
neighbors here. I think we should be with them.

314
00:30:33,665 --> 00:30:35,109
You're sure?

315
00:30:38,462 --> 00:30:41,802
Thank you for coming to find us.

316
00:30:48,941 --> 00:30:52,874
Surely there's no time to celebrating already.

317
00:30:53,637 --> 00:31:01,707
Well, I just wanted to inform you that I shall be giving a briefing
of the situation as we know it to everyone at 6.00 hours.

318
00:31:01,708 --> 00:31:03,446
Everyone, Charles?

319
00:31:04,419 --> 00:31:06,856
The Europeans.

320
00:31:07,839 --> 00:31:10,407
The indication are that it is a coup.

321
00:31:10,408 --> 00:31:14,831
There's also a word that the detachment
of French regime may be sent here.

322
00:31:14,832 --> 00:31:17,156
Reinforcements?

323
00:31:18,921 --> 00:31:21,653
In case of a need to evacuate.

324
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:29,561
It may become unattainable to provide
security for these many Tutsi.

325
00:31:30,914 --> 00:31:34,759
Around here we just call them Rwandans.

326
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,844
Who is in charge here?

327
00:31:39,487 --> 00:31:41,361
My name is Ingulimziwa.

328
00:31:41,362 --> 00:31:44,212
I am the former minister of
this so-called government.

329
00:31:44,213 --> 00:31:50,640
And I must tell you that the killing going on
outside is not simply random. This is all planned.

330
00:31:50,641 --> 00:31:53,358
You must alert your superiors in New York.

331
00:31:53,359 --> 00:31:55,445
You must intervene.

332
00:31:55,870 --> 00:31:59,602
Sir, we are here as peace monitors, nothing more.

333
00:31:59,603 --> 00:32:01,483
There's no mandate for anything else.

334
00:32:01,484 --> 00:32:07,587
Captain, you're no doubt aware what
the Nazis attempted to do with the Jews.

335
00:32:07,588 --> 00:32:08,588
Of course.

336
00:32:08,589 --> 00:32:10,988
This is what we are facing here.

337
00:32:10,989 --> 00:32:15,956
These Hutu extremists, who have taken
control, even call this "the Tutsi problem".

338
00:32:15,957 --> 00:32:18,182
They plan to wipe the Tutsi out.

339
00:32:18,183 --> 00:32:19,638
Do you understand me?

340
00:32:19,639 --> 00:32:20,899
All of them.

341
00:32:22,211 --> 00:32:24,412
She says, she was hiding behind her house.

342
00:32:25,542 --> 00:32:27,962
There were Interahamwe in the streets.

343
00:32:27,963 --> 00:32:28,682
Intera what?

344
00:32:28,683 --> 00:32:30,485
Militias, gangs of militia.

345
00:32:30,625 --> 00:32:32,888
Interahamwe means "those who strike together".

346
00:32:32,889 --> 00:32:37,824
They were checking identity cards, like this.

347
00:32:37,990 --> 00:32:40,577
She said she was very scared
because she's a Tutsi.

348
00:32:42,298 --> 00:32:45,373
She saw one woman and her baby girl.

349
00:32:48,139 --> 00:32:52,650
They kicked the woman in the stomach
and began to take off her clothes.

350
00:32:52,651 --> 00:32:59,596
One of them took the baby by the feet and
swung her against the tree, so the baby hit her had.

351
00:33:03,017 --> 00:33:07,659
They kept swinging
until the baby was dead.

352
00:33:17,589 --> 00:33:19,743
Listen to me, you are safe here.

353
00:33:20,925 --> 00:33:22,249
But I'm Tutsi.

354
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:27,696
If we all stay together in here then we're safe.
There's too many people here, alright?

355
00:33:28,393 --> 00:33:29,840
Alright?

356
00:33:30,858 --> 00:33:32,291
I promise you.

357
00:33:32,292 --> 00:33:36,516
There has been some rumour
and speculations around.

358
00:33:36,517 --> 00:33:39,551
I'll ask you to disregard anything but the facts.

359
00:33:39,996 --> 00:33:42,969
Our best analysis is that a coup has occurred.

360
00:33:42,970 --> 00:33:47,393
We've been assured that an government
will be restored very soon in the meantime.

361
00:33:47,394 --> 00:33:50,358
We are on full contact with your embassies.

362
00:33:50,359 --> 00:33:55,434
And of course an evacuation protocol
is being put into effect.

363
00:33:55,435 --> 00:33:56,464
What does he say?

364
00:33:56,465 --> 00:33:59,414
He says everything is going to be alright.

365
00:33:59,415 --> 00:34:02,856
My father would like to speak to you.

366
00:34:09,002 --> 00:34:10,816
One at a time.

367
00:34:12,289 --> 00:34:14,331
We have organized ourselves.

368
00:34:14,332 --> 00:34:19,008
There will be three groups, one will be security,
watching people who are coming in.

369
00:34:19,112 --> 00:34:22,298
We have some people here
who are embassy workers.

370
00:34:22,299 --> 00:34:24,179
And the third group will do food.

371
00:34:24,180 --> 00:34:25,797
Okay good, that's great.

372
00:34:25,798 --> 00:34:29,153
We have all agreed that we shall only
have one meal a day. That's at 4 o'clock.

373
00:34:29,154 --> 00:34:35,558
So we need a steady food supply and something to measure
the right food. Can you find these things for us, please?

374
00:34:35,559 --> 00:34:37,535
Sure. I can ask father Christopher.

375
00:34:37,536 --> 00:34:38,783
- Thank you.
- Okay.

376
00:34:46,226 --> 00:34:46,766
Hi.

377
00:34:47,822 --> 00:34:52,760
Listen, they’re doing a really good job outside, organizing
themselves, but they're gonna need some stuff from us.

378
00:34:52,761 --> 00:34:55,466
Fine. I'll see to that after Mass.

379
00:34:55,467 --> 00:34:56,661
The Mass?

380
00:34:56,662 --> 00:34:59,232
I am priest in a catholic country, Joe.

381
00:34:59,233 --> 00:35:01,715
This is what I do.

382
00:35:02,761 --> 00:35:04,494
It's in the job description.

383
00:35:04,495 --> 00:35:05,534
Yeah, sure.

384
00:35:05,535 --> 00:35:08,152
Do you think it's the best time for that?

385
00:35:08,153 --> 00:35:11,669
Time's a stress, people need to commune with God.

386
00:35:11,814 --> 00:35:13,954
I think maybe they'll prefer some food.

387
00:35:13,955 --> 00:35:15,928
Water, just put a reassurance.

388
00:35:15,929 --> 00:35:18,645
Well, come to Mass.

389
00:35:18,646 --> 00:35:21,618
Get all free on the same ticket.

390
00:36:41,035 --> 00:36:44,647
It's been a 10th night here
in Rwandan capital Kigali.

391
00:36:44,648 --> 00:36:47,501
The normally bustling streets
are now completely deserted.

392
00:36:47,502 --> 00:36:50,838
Except for angry soldiers,
loyal to the former president.

393
00:36:50,839 --> 00:36:52,814
...and shooting bodies is becoming common.

394
00:36:52,815 --> 00:36:56,794
Militias with machetes and clubs rule the streets.

395
00:36:56,795 --> 00:37:03,752
And what appears to have been a deliberate plan to
massacre Tutsis. Thousands have now been executed.

396
00:37:05,660 --> 00:37:09,414
- Councilor.
- Father Christopher.

397
00:37:09,415 --> 00:37:14,059
These are difficult times,
such uncertainties.

398
00:37:14,060 --> 00:37:15,683
Please, be careful.

399
00:37:15,684 --> 00:37:18,583
Tutsis have spies everywhere.

400
00:37:18,584 --> 00:37:20,119
Some might even be in your school.

401
00:37:21,416 --> 00:37:24,688
I appreciate your concern
for our welfare, councilor.

402
00:37:24,689 --> 00:37:28,416
Of course the welfare of
our citizens is paramount.

403
00:37:29,206 --> 00:37:34,218
Well, you could deal some blankets,
a fuel for the generator - that sort of thing.

404
00:37:35,050 --> 00:37:40,593
Perhaps tomorrow, my superior
colonel Bugesera has asked...

405
00:37:40,712 --> 00:37:45,423
He has asked me to ask you, perhaps
have a small word with your Belgian guests.

406
00:37:46,650 --> 00:37:53,068
My government is uncomfortable with the idea of
United Nation soldiers guarding those poor people in your school.

407
00:37:53,069 --> 00:37:56,269
We would prefer Rwandans protecting Rwandans.

408
00:37:58,431 --> 00:38:04,343
Well, I'm not sure that it is my position
to talk to the capitaine about that.

409
00:38:04,344 --> 00:38:07,339
Of course you know him better than I.

410
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:09,357
Though I'm sure he will listen to you.

411
00:38:09,358 --> 00:38:11,787
His mind must be on those missing men.

412
00:38:12,677 --> 00:38:14,529
What missing men?

413
00:38:15,876 --> 00:38:17,573
Ten Belgian UN soldiers.

414
00:38:17,574 --> 00:38:18,870
What?

415
00:38:18,871 --> 00:38:22,382
They were kidnapped while
guarding our Prime Minister.

416
00:38:22,383 --> 00:38:24,976
A terrible business, terrible.

417
00:38:25,881 --> 00:38:30,280
Well, I'll see what I can do.

418
00:38:32,126 --> 00:38:33,822
Thank you.

419
00:38:33,823 --> 00:38:36,207
That would be very nice.

420
00:38:44,056 --> 00:38:47,950
Yes it's true. The detachment of 10 soldiers
were protecting the prime minister.

421
00:38:47,951 --> 00:38:49,796
He said they were kidnapped.

422
00:38:49,797 --> 00:38:52,380
It's possible. We don't know where they are.

423
00:38:52,381 --> 00:38:54,877
So what happened to the prime minister?

424
00:38:54,878 --> 00:38:58,687
She's dead. Murdered.

425
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:34,528
Look, it might sound weird, right.
But what about this.

426
00:39:34,529 --> 00:39:42,395
We could call a bishop and get him to come to this school,
not to give a Mass but for a talk or symbol, you know.

427
00:39:42,396 --> 00:39:45,159
It's not gonna make any difference.

428
00:39:46,102 --> 00:39:51,758
Wait a minute, you can think about it.
You know him well so call him, get him round here.

429
00:39:51,759 --> 00:39:53,595
I don't think so, Joe.

430
00:39:53,596 --> 00:39:56,586
Well look, if he came then what kind
of signal will that send out?

431
00:39:56,587 --> 00:39:57,625
Gods.

432
00:39:57,626 --> 00:39:59,639
I know you don't think we can make a difference.

433
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:03,189
We passed all that!

434
00:40:08,322 --> 00:40:11,412
If the UN now being targeted.

435
00:40:13,036 --> 00:40:16,090
Then we are way beyond that.

436
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:23,296
I must call sister Isabel again.

437
00:40:38,151 --> 00:40:39,680
What's he saying?

438
00:40:41,579 --> 00:40:43,950
Who will fill the empty graves?

439
00:40:43,951 --> 00:40:47,328
The cockroaches are hiding in the churches.

440
00:40:47,329 --> 00:40:49,969
They are hiding in the schools.

441
00:41:22,516 --> 00:41:23,495
What's going on?

442
00:41:23,496 --> 00:41:24,639
Food.

443
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:27,960
They are discussing how to rush and what's left.

444
00:41:28,481 --> 00:41:29,430
Can we have a word?

445
00:41:33,192 --> 00:41:37,517
Don't bite my head off,
but I have an idea.

446
00:41:37,518 --> 00:41:39,351
Nobody knows what's happening here right?

447
00:41:40,886 --> 00:41:42,370
So we should get on the TV cameras.

448
00:41:43,094 --> 00:41:44,946
What would that do?

449
00:41:44,947 --> 00:41:51,322
You know, nothing exist if it's not on TV. So we get the cameras
in here and the rest of the world sees what's happening.

450
00:41:51,323 --> 00:41:52,853
And they'll have to do something.

451
00:41:52,854 --> 00:41:54,107
How do we achieve that?

452
00:41:54,108 --> 00:41:58,603
I can go and get Rachel Watson,
she's with the BBC. Staying at the Morahl.

453
00:42:01,312 --> 00:42:03,574
But I can't let you go outside alone.

454
00:42:03,575 --> 00:42:05,811
Fine, I'll get the UN to give me an escort.

455
00:42:06,746 --> 00:42:07,667
Okay.

456
00:42:08,690 --> 00:42:09,604
Great.

457
00:42:10,442 --> 00:42:12,979
I'm sorry my central command would never agree.

458
00:42:12,980 --> 00:42:18,716
Charles, your mandate is about peacekeeping.
If you help me get the BBC and that will help to keep the peace.

459
00:42:18,717 --> 00:42:20,434
You know that.

460
00:42:20,435 --> 00:42:21,633
Just one vehicle.

461
00:42:21,634 --> 00:42:22,823
Just one.

462
00:42:23,477 --> 00:42:24,297
It's possible.

463
00:42:24,298 --> 00:42:25,447
Give me a minute.

464
00:42:36,843 --> 00:42:38,984
- Charles.
- No escort.

465
00:42:38,985 --> 00:42:40,010
But you just said...

466
00:42:40,011 --> 00:42:42,097
No escort! Leave now.

467
00:42:42,932 --> 00:42:45,268
What a fuck is that!

468
00:42:47,660 --> 00:42:48,962
They don't give me an escort.

469
00:42:48,963 --> 00:42:52,686
I'm going get Francois at his dad's place.
He's Hutu, so, you know.... He's with me.

470
00:42:52,687 --> 00:42:55,683
- Everybody knows this truck anyway.
- Wait here.

471
00:43:06,388 --> 00:43:08,971
Our missing soldiers have been found.

472
00:43:08,972 --> 00:43:12,547
They were taken to a government
barracks and executed.

473
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:14,011
Executed?

474
00:43:14,012 --> 00:43:15,912
Butchered.

475
00:43:18,898 --> 00:43:20,810
Oh my God, I'm so sorry.

476
00:43:23,004 --> 00:43:27,563
You realize it? No one safety
can be guaranteed now.

477
00:43:48,018 --> 00:43:53,064
The time has come to do your duty!

478
00:43:55,846 --> 00:44:01,371
The army cannot do their job alone,
it is up to you the people!

479
00:44:01,372 --> 00:44:06,091
Go to the roads.
Work at the roadblocks!

480
00:44:07,888 --> 00:44:09,016
Is Francois here?

481
00:44:09,017 --> 00:44:10,524
No thank you.

482
00:44:10,525 --> 00:44:11,821
Is Francois ... Thank you.

483
00:44:11,822 --> 00:44:14,515
Francois.

484
00:44:15,963 --> 00:44:18,156
Madame, is your son here?

485
00:44:44,059 --> 00:44:47,132
The news are screaming for
two ways every half hour, Joe.

486
00:44:47,133 --> 00:44:49,079
From 9 to 3 minutes for me tonight.

487
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:51,888
There are over 1,5 thousand
people hiding at school.

488
00:44:51,889 --> 00:44:56,117
Yeah, there's 2000 Tutsis hiding at Sainte Familie
and God knows how many at the stadium as well.

489
00:44:56,274 --> 00:45:00,263
We also have about 40 Europeans, hiding.

490
00:45:01,130 --> 00:45:04,292
When it started off it was just
the army doing the killings.

491
00:45:04,293 --> 00:45:09,779
No it's spreading to everyone, they're all killing
Tutsis - the ordinary people, police, everyone.

492
00:45:09,780 --> 00:45:12,015
I haven't seen such fucking machetes in my life.

493
00:45:12,947 --> 00:45:14,515
Fuck, the militia.

494
00:45:14,516 --> 00:45:15,799
Interahamwe.

495
00:45:16,279 --> 00:45:17,234
Oh, shit!

496
00:45:17,299 --> 00:45:18,829
Everyone around here knows us.

497
00:45:18,830 --> 00:45:20,421
Lucky us.

498
00:45:27,462 --> 00:45:29,209
Stop.

499
00:46:02,004 --> 00:46:03,427
Okay.

500
00:46:08,753 --> 00:46:09,546
No.

501
00:46:20,102 --> 00:46:22,464
Just take the tape back.
You push the blue button on the top.

502
00:46:42,689 --> 00:46:43,922
I'll show you...

503
00:46:43,923 --> 00:46:44,767
BBC.

504
00:47:08,586 --> 00:47:10,585
Joe, look at me.

505
00:47:10,586 --> 00:47:12,387
Keep looking at me. Alright?

506
00:47:14,396 --> 00:47:15,565
Look at me.

