524
00:51:15,404 --> 00:51:17,841
I'm sorry.

525
00:51:20,993 --> 00:51:24,125
Capitaine Delon, how do you
view the situation now?

526
00:51:24,126 --> 00:51:30,260
Extremist Hutu elements are targeting the
Tutsi minority and anyone who supports them.

527
00:51:30,261 --> 00:51:33,912
You know there are people being
killed right outside these gates.

528
00:51:33,913 --> 00:51:35,103
Yes.

529
00:51:35,104 --> 00:51:38,460
So why can't the UN stop this slaughter?

530
00:51:38,461 --> 00:51:40,566
We do not have a mandate for that.

531
00:51:40,567 --> 00:51:42,834
We can only fire if fired upon.

532
00:51:42,835 --> 00:51:44,627
The parameters of our operation are very clear.

533
00:51:44,628 --> 00:51:47,714
Some people are starting to call this
a genocide. Would you call it that?

534
00:51:48,712 --> 00:51:50,288
Well...

535
00:51:50,674 --> 00:51:54,929
Because you know that if this is genocide
you are obligated to intervene.

536
00:51:56,011 --> 00:51:57,641
Stop the camera, please.

537
00:51:57,642 --> 00:51:59,822
Stop it now!

538
00:52:02,402 --> 00:52:04,448
What's going on here
is not my choice, okay?

539
00:52:04,449 --> 00:52:07,199
Being here and doing nothing
is also not my choice.

540
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:10,844
I'm a military commandor with a
mandate to observe. I can do no more.

541
00:52:10,845 --> 00:52:12,197
You are the UN, show it.

542
00:52:12,198 --> 00:52:13,722
But I'm not the Security Council.

543
00:52:13,723 --> 00:52:14,982
They make our mandate.

544
00:52:14,983 --> 00:52:23,172
Why don't you call New York and get a chance, because, let me
tell you, we have tried. And please, let me know how far you get.

545
00:52:56,070 --> 00:52:58,897
There are Interahamwe outside both gates now.

546
00:53:00,372 --> 00:53:03,284
It'd be as well being story surrounded.

547
00:53:04,898 --> 00:53:09,719
You know I just don't understand
why did they kill those UN soldiers?

548
00:53:11,269 --> 00:53:13,427
What a stupid people.

549
00:53:14,620 --> 00:53:18,011
They must have known
it'd have repercussions.

550
00:53:18,012 --> 00:53:21,760
Perhaps they wanted repercussions.

551
00:53:25,873 --> 00:53:31,915
In Somalia 18 Americans died.
It was enough to force a complete withdraw.

552
00:53:32,049 --> 00:53:35,315
As you see these are not stupid people.

553
00:53:37,099 --> 00:53:40,726
Will the UN withdraw?
What you think, Charles?

554
00:53:40,727 --> 00:53:43,647
At the moment my orders
are to remain in position.

555
00:53:43,648 --> 00:53:46,042
But if your orders change?

556
00:53:47,638 --> 00:53:48,897
I'm a soldier.

557
00:53:53,554 --> 00:53:56,901
Can't imagine what
it must be like for you.

558
00:53:56,902 --> 00:54:02,874
Whoever wanted to talk.
If any of your men ever wanted to talk.

559
00:54:17,091 --> 00:54:22,307
My grandparents were Belgian, from Mehanen.

560
00:54:22,308 --> 00:54:30,202
When the Nazis came through that town, they took
in as many Jews as they could 20, maybe 30 people.

561
00:54:31,193 --> 00:54:42,398
Everyone asked to hand them over. But my grandparents
saved those people. I was always proud of that.

562
00:54:57,099 --> 00:54:59,593
Stop it!

563
00:55:00,709 --> 00:55:02,978
Stop it immediately!

564
00:55:02,979 --> 00:55:04,569
What's going here?

565
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:07,455
He was walking across over there with a machete.

566
00:55:08,080 --> 00:55:09,689
He is Interahamwe.

567
00:55:16,777 --> 00:55:20,556
You all stay calm.

568
00:55:24,708 --> 00:55:29,521
You all stay calm.

569
00:55:43,475 --> 00:55:45,653
Are you alright?

570
00:55:45,654 --> 00:55:48,139
I'm afraid, Joe.

571
00:55:48,140 --> 00:55:51,740
- Everything's alright here.
- For you maybe.

572
00:55:53,090 --> 00:55:57,514
See that woman there, her name is Rachel.
She's with the television crew.

573
00:55:57,515 --> 00:56:02,391
And they gonna film us. If they are
filming us, no one can touch us.

574
00:56:39,483 --> 00:56:40,483
You're okay?

575
00:56:44,728 --> 00:56:46,596
Why did you come here?

576
00:56:51,997 --> 00:56:54,018
You know, growing up...

577
00:56:54,019 --> 00:56:56,025
I had everything that kid can want.

578
00:56:56,283 --> 00:57:01,245
And... it's just me trying to say
"thank you" I guess.

579
00:57:03,532 --> 00:57:07,582
Trying to make a difference.

580
00:57:08,957 --> 00:57:18,780
I know it. I catch myself sometimes thinking
"well done, Joe. You are really doing it."

581
00:57:20,167 --> 00:57:23,148
You are starring in your own film.

582
00:57:25,949 --> 00:57:28,899
And then there's all this.

583
00:57:30,761 --> 00:57:35,333
Last year in Bosnia
I felt exactly the same way.

584
00:57:35,334 --> 00:57:36,382
How was that?

585
00:57:36,383 --> 00:57:37,906
Great actually.

586
00:57:37,907 --> 00:57:39,339
Best stuff I've ever done.

587
00:57:41,928 --> 00:57:43,733
Cried every day.

588
00:57:45,501 --> 00:57:50,728
Strangely enough over here... not a tear.

589
00:57:50,729 --> 00:57:54,180
I guess you get on to it.

590
00:57:56,675 --> 00:57:57,639
No.

591
00:57:58,212 --> 00:58:00,305
Just worse than that.

592
00:58:00,306 --> 00:58:10,766
Anytime I saw a dead Bosnian woman,
white woman, I feel... that could be my mom.

593
00:58:10,886 --> 00:58:18,070
Over here they're just dead Africans.

594
00:58:23,337 --> 00:58:24,831
All things the same.

595
00:58:26,872 --> 00:58:30,346
We're all just selfish pieces of work.

596
00:58:34,034 --> 00:58:37,269
- Shit. What the fuck is that?
- That's all right. It's just the generators.

597
00:58:37,270 --> 00:58:40,042
I'm surprised that didn't happen already.

598
00:58:46,518 --> 00:58:47,811
Okay.

599
00:58:53,218 --> 00:58:55,673
- Where is it coming from?
- It's there.

600
00:59:17,217 --> 00:59:19,473
Breathe and push!

601
00:59:19,474 --> 00:59:21,306
Good girl.

602
00:59:21,307 --> 00:59:22,843
Breathe.

603
00:59:22,844 --> 00:59:25,306
Push!

604
00:59:25,307 --> 00:59:27,336
Breathe and push.

605
00:59:27,337 --> 00:59:28,134
Remember to breathe.

606
00:59:28,135 --> 00:59:28,971
Push!

607
00:59:29,390 --> 00:59:30,560
We have the head.

608
00:59:30,561 --> 00:59:32,953
Push!

609
00:59:32,954 --> 00:59:34,839
Oh yes. Push!

610
00:59:34,840 --> 00:59:36,765
Push Edda, you are doing really well. Come on.

611
00:59:36,766 --> 00:59:41,382
Push!

612
00:59:59,136 --> 01:00:02,460
She wants to call the baby Christopher.

613
01:00:05,806 --> 01:00:08,121
Thank you.

614
01:00:47,706 --> 01:00:50,498
I think, Christopher is an awful name.

615
01:00:52,964 --> 01:00:55,972
The fathers at Yamata have been murdered.

616
01:00:55,973 --> 01:00:57,944
In that church.

617
01:00:58,998 --> 01:01:00,119
What?

618
01:01:00,619 --> 01:01:02,445
Father Jean?

619
01:01:02,446 --> 01:01:07,565
And all the parishioners. Hacked to death.

620
01:01:07,693 --> 01:01:09,290
Jesus Christ.

621
01:01:13,366 --> 01:01:16,307
I have not seen this before.

622
01:01:18,592 --> 01:01:21,756
Did you get to the convent?

623
01:01:21,757 --> 01:01:23,801
The line is dead.

624
01:01:31,810 --> 01:01:33,116
What you're doing?

625
01:01:33,778 --> 01:01:36,923
I've set Mass every Monday
with that convent for 12 years.

626
01:01:38,540 --> 01:01:39,551
Christopher.

627
01:01:39,552 --> 01:01:41,100
I have to go.

628
01:01:41,101 --> 01:01:44,374
It's not gonna make any difference
that you're priest or you are white.

629
01:01:44,375 --> 01:01:46,673
They don't care who you are anymore.

630
01:01:46,674 --> 01:01:51,311
- I'll be aright.
- You won't be alright. I've been out there and it's falling apart.

631
01:01:54,321 --> 01:01:56,434
They might already be dead.

632
01:01:58,298 --> 01:02:00,468
That's not the point.

633
01:02:02,915 --> 01:02:05,115
This baby is not well.

634
01:02:08,928 --> 01:02:10,270
He has a fewer.

635
01:02:10,271 --> 01:02:13,430
There's also discharge
coming from his eyes.

636
01:02:13,881 --> 01:02:16,271
There's nothing here.

637
01:02:16,272 --> 01:02:18,294
You know exactly what we need?

638
01:02:18,295 --> 01:02:20,110
Yes.

639
01:02:25,043 --> 01:02:28,977
- First the medicine, then the convent.
- You don't have to do this, you know.

640
01:02:28,978 --> 01:02:30,744
Yes I do, Joe.

641
01:03:39,362 --> 01:03:41,716
Good morning, Julius.

642
01:03:42,353 --> 01:03:43,343
Good morning.

643
01:03:43,812 --> 01:03:45,322
I need some medicine.

644
01:03:48,605 --> 01:03:51,111
We have some, I think.

645
01:04:01,066 --> 01:04:03,119
What is the child's name?

646
01:04:03,120 --> 01:04:06,526
Christopher.

647
01:04:07,053 --> 01:04:09,708
Do you have the medicine?

648
01:04:09,709 --> 01:04:12,705
And what is the child's address?

649
01:04:17,654 --> 01:04:20,979
Do you have the medicine?

650
01:04:27,765 --> 01:04:29,401
Follow me.

651
01:04:40,560 --> 01:04:44,393
This child is Hutu or Tutsi?

652
01:04:47,171 --> 01:04:48,242
Hutu.

653
01:04:51,691 --> 01:04:53,021
Wait here.

654
01:05:21,888 --> 01:05:26,342
I knew I had it.
It will help him.

655
01:05:27,969 --> 01:05:30,488
Take a lot of care out there.

656
01:05:34,598 --> 01:05:36,008
Thank you.

657
01:06:06,496 --> 01:06:08,539
Father Christopher.

658
01:06:11,759 --> 01:06:14,738
It's me, remember the hurdles?

659
01:06:18,393 --> 01:06:19,686
You see?

660
01:06:28,960 --> 01:06:29,889
Don't.

661
01:06:29,890 --> 01:06:32,731
No, it's medicine.

662
01:06:32,732 --> 01:06:35,069
Medicine?

663
01:06:35,070 --> 01:06:35,894
It is my medicine.

664
01:08:48,258 --> 01:08:49,907
Christopher.

665
01:08:52,676 --> 01:08:56,670
We need you to tell the rest of the school
that we are having problems with the dogs.

666
01:08:56,671 --> 01:08:57,861
Dogs?

667
01:08:57,862 --> 01:09:01,295
The dogs, outside the gate,
eating the bodies.

668
01:09:01,296 --> 01:09:05,381
Can you please just inform everyone
that we have a health problem here.

669
01:09:05,382 --> 01:09:07,737
We are going to shoot the dogs.

670
01:09:07,877 --> 01:09:10,750
If they hear gunshots,
they should not panic. Okay?

671
01:09:10,751 --> 01:09:13,392
Did they open fire?

672
01:09:13,393 --> 01:09:16,704
Did they open fire, Charles?

673
01:09:16,705 --> 01:09:19,091
Did who open fire?

674
01:09:19,092 --> 01:09:21,062
The dogs.

675
01:09:23,478 --> 01:09:25,683
Were they shooting at you?

676
01:09:25,684 --> 01:09:27,286
What are you talking about?

677
01:09:28,009 --> 01:09:37,485
This is according to your mandate, if you are going to shoot
the dogs then the dogs must have been shooting at you first.

678
01:09:37,486 --> 01:09:38,245
Please...

679
01:09:38,246 --> 01:09:39,647
I'll tell you what.

680
01:09:39,648 --> 01:09:45,151
Why don't we just say
'fuck the mandate'?!

681
01:09:45,152 --> 01:09:49,358
And when you're finished with this health problem
maybe you'll address the other health problem?

682
01:09:49,359 --> 01:09:51,579
The one over there!

683
01:09:52,567 --> 01:09:55,909
With that fucking machetes.

684
01:10:11,574 --> 01:10:14,325
We have no more fuel for the fire.

685
01:10:17,623 --> 01:10:19,355
Use the Bibles.

686
01:10:20,619 --> 01:10:23,643
We'd end go around if we share. Come on.

687
01:10:29,273 --> 01:10:31,156
Christopher.

688
01:10:33,052 --> 01:10:35,244
You know what, Joe.

689
01:10:35,383 --> 01:10:39,895
People have been coming to Mass
here for God knows how long.

690
01:10:39,896 --> 01:10:45,252
They get up, they go to church, they sing,
they eat the bread and then they leave.

691
01:10:45,908 --> 01:10:48,055
Do you know why?

692
01:10:49,302 --> 01:10:52,646
Because they are told to.

693
01:10:56,014 --> 01:11:02,386
They just go through the motions without the
slightest understanding of what it is they are engaged in.

694
01:11:02,387 --> 01:11:11,002
Whether they are being told to eat a wafer
or hack their own flesh and blood to death.

695
01:11:11,003 --> 01:11:12,901
You are wrong, father.

696
01:11:13,833 --> 01:11:16,739
I know you've made a difference.

697
01:11:19,013 --> 01:11:22,613
I spent 30 years on this bloody continent.

698
01:11:22,614 --> 01:11:25,536
The only thing we ever had that
ever stayed the same was hope.

699
01:11:26,395 --> 01:11:28,378
I always had hope, Joe.

700
01:11:28,379 --> 01:11:32,773
In fact this is all we ever had.

701
01:11:32,969 --> 01:11:36,360
Now...

702
01:11:36,498 --> 01:11:39,231
...nothing.

703
01:11:39,426 --> 01:11:41,377
We are running dry.

704
01:12:09,413 --> 01:12:14,198
Do you receive, Christopher into
the congregation of Christ's flock?

705
01:12:14,199 --> 01:12:18,928
And so sign him with
the sign of the cross.

706
01:12:18,929 --> 01:12:25,091
And intook on that here after he shall not be
ashamed to confess the faith of Christ crucified.

707
01:12:25,092 --> 01:12:31,855
The man will lead his fight under his
banner against sin, the world and the devil.

708
01:12:31,856 --> 01:12:35,520
And he will continue as Christ
faithful soldier and servant...

709
01:12:38,111 --> 01:12:41,804
...until his life's end.

710
01:12:43,221 --> 01:12:43,901
Amen.

711
01:12:56,418 --> 01:12:58,278
It's the French.

712
01:14:23,688 --> 01:14:25,839
Bastards, they’re only taking the whites.

713
01:14:25,840 --> 01:14:26,665
What?

714
01:14:26,666 --> 01:14:28,403
They are only taking the whites.

715
01:14:28,404 --> 01:14:33,431
- But they can't do it.
- Until your Capitaine stated, they were only taking French.

716
01:14:33,466 --> 01:14:36,639
Excuse me, is there room for me on this truck?

717
01:14:36,640 --> 01:14:37,640
If you hurry up - yes.

718
01:14:37,641 --> 01:14:40,847
Then I wanna donate my place to one of
these people. Her name is Marie Motagoma.

719
01:14:40,848 --> 01:14:42,577
No, no Rwandans.

720
01:15:22,495 --> 01:15:25,398
Joe, come on, get on this truck.

721
01:15:27,076 --> 01:15:30,496
For fuck sake, Joe, there's
nothing more you can do here.

722
01:15:33,540 --> 01:15:35,610
I'm staying.

723
01:17:10,526 --> 01:17:15,457
I believe in God, the Father Almighty,
creator of heaven and earth.

724
01:17:15,579 --> 01:17:20,645
I believe in Jesus Christ,
his Son, the Lord.

725
01:17:26,141 --> 01:17:27,746
Keep going.

726
01:17:31,892 --> 01:17:33,820
Does he love everyone?

727
01:17:34,485 --> 01:17:38,453
Does he even love those men
on the roads outside?

728
01:17:42,914 --> 01:17:47,159
God does not always
like everything we do.

729
01:17:47,160 --> 01:17:48,956
That's our choice.

730
01:17:49,445 --> 01:17:51,938
But he loves all his children.

731
01:18:04,677 --> 01:18:06,250
Has anybody seen Edda?

732
01:18:06,251 --> 01:18:09,866
Edda, the woman with the baby.

733
01:18:10,716 --> 01:18:12,655
Did you see Edda with the baby?

734
01:18:12,656 --> 01:18:16,577
Cause I have a medicine for the baby.

735
01:18:24,855 --> 01:18:27,713
Claude, have you seen Edda or Aaron?

736
01:18:27,714 --> 01:18:29,525
- They are running away.
- What?

737
01:18:29,526 --> 01:18:31,637
- Where?
- Over the back field.

738
01:18:55,732 --> 01:18:57,423
Edda.

739
01:19:53,336 --> 01:19:54,866
Don't cry.

740
01:19:55,447 --> 01:19:57,854
Don't cry.

741
01:20:32,024 --> 01:20:35,675
How much pain can a human being take?

742
01:20:37,603 --> 01:20:44,989
If you feel enough pain,
does everything just shut down?

743
01:20:45,398 --> 01:20:47,002
Before you've done it.

744
01:20:48,006 --> 01:20:50,297
I don't know, Joe.

745
01:20:51,125 --> 01:20:52,784
Cause you think no one knew.

746
01:20:52,785 --> 01:20:55,095
You think that it'd be something...

747
01:20:55,096 --> 01:20:58,979
Something that you designed,
you know, shed or fell.

748
01:21:00,476 --> 01:21:03,356
If you feel enough pain.

749
01:21:03,357 --> 01:21:04,963
I hope so.

750
01:21:06,852 --> 01:21:08,804
Yeah, God knows it.

751
01:21:09,542 --> 01:21:12,006
Maybe we should ask him.

752
01:21:13,323 --> 01:21:14,707
He's still around.

753
01:21:21,378 --> 01:21:24,573
I think it's time we pack our bags.

754
01:22:26,520 --> 01:22:28,161
Marie.

755
01:22:35,686 --> 01:22:39,618
You'll never leave us, papa Christopher?

756
01:22:44,467 --> 01:22:47,281
Terrible things may happen
in this world, Marie.

757
01:22:47,282 --> 01:22:54,478
But however terrible they are,
you are in my heart.

758
01:22:54,479 --> 01:22:59,710
And you will be there until I die.

759
01:23:19,941 --> 01:23:23,291
Joe, may I have a word with you?

760
01:23:32,417 --> 01:23:35,250
I have orders to withdraw to the airport.

761
01:23:38,208 --> 01:23:40,949
How long do we have?

762
01:23:40,950 --> 01:23:43,479
We leave in 30 minutes.

763
01:23:48,173 --> 01:23:52,840
Joe, you must come. If you do not
come you will die, it's very simple.

764
01:23:52,841 --> 01:23:54,940
What about these people?

765
01:23:57,324 --> 01:24:00,695
You must understand,
